steps.description:
In the two front and two back cans in the rows of cans, make a mark about halfway down each can at the place where the cans would face each other when placed side by side. The marks must be exactly opposite each other, to ensure even joining, both ends. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/b/b2/Make-Beer-Can-Christmas-Ornaments-Step-11Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Make-Beer-Can-Christmas-Ornaments-Step-11Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/b/b2/Make-Beer-Can-Christmas-Ornaments-Step-11Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Make-Beer-Can-Christmas-Ornaments-Step-11Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":307,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":507.3626373626374,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/2.5/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Pierce holes at these marks and insert a piece of dowel about 3 inches (7.5cm) in length into the cans on one row. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/3/38/Make-Beer-Can-Christmas-Ornaments-Step-11Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Make-Beer-Can-Christmas-Ornaments-Step-11Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/3/38/Make-Beer-Can-Christmas-Ornaments-Step-11Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Make-Beer-Can-Christmas-Ornaments-Step-11Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":307,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":507.3626373626374,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/2.5/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Next, slip the dowel into the holes of the cans in the other row to join the two rows together. It's a good idea to add a dollop of glue too, to ensure the dowels don't shift when the ornament is hung or displayed. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/78/Make-Beer-Can-Christmas-Ornaments-Step-11Bullet3.jpg/v4-460px-Make-Beer-Can-Christmas-Ornaments-Step-11Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/78/Make-Beer-Can-Christmas-Ornaments-Step-11Bullet3.jpg/v4-760px-Make-Beer-Can-Christmas-Ornaments-Step-11Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":307,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":507.3626373626374,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/2.5/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

The reindeer are now assembled. You'll get to decorate them shortly. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/6/63/Make-Beer-Can-Christmas-Ornaments-Step-11Bullet4.jpg/v4-460px-Make-Beer-Can-Christmas-Ornaments-Step-11Bullet4.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/6/63/Make-Beer-Can-Christmas-Ornaments-Step-11Bullet4.jpg/v4-760px-Make-Beer-Can-Christmas-Ornaments-Step-11Bullet4.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":307,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":507.3626373626374,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/2.5/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Find some strong wire and cut into two pieces about 4 inches (10cm) in length. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/a/aa/Make-Beer-Can-Christmas-Ornaments-Step-12Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Make-Beer-Can-Christmas-Ornaments-Step-12Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/a/aa/Make-Beer-Can-Christmas-Ornaments-Step-12Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Make-Beer-Can-Christmas-Ornaments-Step-12Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":307,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":507.3626373626374,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/2.5/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Pierce a hole into each can at the end of the reindeer set and insert the wires, one into each can. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/c/c8/Make-Beer-Can-Christmas-Ornaments-Step-12Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Make-Beer-Can-Christmas-Ornaments-Step-12Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/c/c8/Make-Beer-Can-Christmas-Ornaments-Step-12Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Make-Beer-Can-Christmas-Ornaments-Step-12Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":307,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":507.3626373626374,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/2.5/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Turn the sleigh can onto its side, lid end facing the reindeer. Then pierce two equivalent holes into the lid of the sleigh at to evenly spaced places in the middle half of the lid circle. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/b/b8/Make-Beer-Can-Christmas-Ornaments-Step-12Bullet3.jpg/v4-460px-Make-Beer-Can-Christmas-Ornaments-Step-12Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/b/b8/Make-Beer-Can-Christmas-Ornaments-Step-12Bullet3.jpg/v4-760px-Make-Beer-Can-Christmas-Ornaments-Step-12Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":307,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":507.3626373626374,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/2.5/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Check that the sleigh is held firmly to the reindeer––it should be hovering about halfway against the upright reindeer cans, in the air. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/3/34/Make-Beer-Can-Christmas-Ornaments-Step-12Bullet4.jpg/v4-460px-Make-Beer-Can-Christmas-Ornaments-Step-12Bullet4.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/3/34/Make-Beer-Can-Christmas-Ornaments-Step-12Bullet4.jpg/v4-760px-Make-Beer-Can-Christmas-Ornaments-Step-12Bullet4.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":307,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":507.3626373626374,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/2.5/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

For the reins, glue two long pieces of string either side of the front of the reindeer sets and bring the string up to Santa's hands (or as near an approximation of his hands as possible given your figurine). {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/57/Make-Beer-Can-Christmas-Ornaments-Step-15Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Make-Beer-Can-Christmas-Ornaments-Step-15Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/57/Make-Beer-Can-Christmas-Ornaments-Step-15Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Make-Beer-Can-Christmas-Ornaments-Step-15Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":307,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":507.3626373626374,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/2.5/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

To hang the ornament, attach a long piece of string tied to middle of the dowels in the reindeer sets and to the end of the Santa sleigh (you can use heavy duty glue or pierce two small holes in the end of Santa's sleigh and thread the string through and tie a knot). {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/56/Make-Beer-Can-Christmas-Ornaments-Step-15Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Make-Beer-Can-Christmas-Ornaments-Step-15Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/56/Make-Beer-Can-Christmas-Ornaments-Step-15Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Make-Beer-Can-Christmas-Ornaments-Step-15Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":307,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":507.3626373626374,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/2.5/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}
